  <h2>Cultural Heritage of Bihar</h2>
  <p class="subtitle">Explore the traditions, festivals, arts, music, and cuisine of Bihar.</p>

  <div class="culture-cards">
    <div class="culture-card">
      <img src="/images/madhubani-art.jpeg" alt="Madhubani Art">
      <h3>Madhubani Art</h3>
      <p>Traditional Mithila painting style that reflects folk culture and rituals.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="culture-card">
      <img src="/images/chhath.jpeg" alt="Chhath Puja">
      <h3>Chhath Puja</h3>
      <p>Major festival dedicated to the Sun God, celebrated with great devotion across Bihar.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="culture-card">
      <img src="/images/litti-chokha.jpeg" alt="Litti Chokha">
      <h3>Litti Chokha</h3>
      <p>The signature dish of Bihar made from sattu, roasted over fire and served with chokha.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="culture-card">
      <img src="/images/jat-jatin.jpeg" alt="Folk Dance">
      <h3>Folk Dances</h3>
      <p>Traditional dances like Jat-Jatin, Bidesia, and Sohar performed during cultural events.</p>
    </div>
